on%20the%20FTX%20exchange.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlameda's%20deep-rooted%20relationship%20with%20FTX%20goes%20back%20to%20the%20exchange's%20beginnings.%20Before%20FTX%20had%20its%20own%20bank%20accounts%2C%20the%20customer%20deposits%20were%20wired%20straight%20into%20an%20account%20owned%20by%20Alameda%2C%20which%20had%20an%20easier%20time%20opening%20accounts%20with%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20unlike%20any%20other%20user%20on%20FTX%2C%20Alameda's%20main%20sub-account%20had%20a%20%2465%20billion%20line%20of%20credit%2C%20which%20effectively%20allowed%20the%20crypto%20hedge%20fund%20to%20borrow%20unlimited%20amounts%20of%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20Alameda%20account%20had%20a%20balance%2C%20on%20average%2C%20of%20negative%20%242%20billion%20throughout%202021%2C%20Bankman-Fried%20testified.%20It%20was%20OK%2C%20he%20said%2C%20because%20the%20company%20had%20assets%20in%20places%20outside%20FTX%2C%20and%20their%20net%20value%20was%20billions%20of%20dollars%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20normal%20customers%20had%20no%20way%20of%20getting%20a%20line%20of%20credit%20on%20FTX%20at%20all.%20On%20the%20witness%20stand%2C%20Bankman-Fried%20could%20name%20only%20one%20other%20institution%20with%20a%20line%20of%20credit%3A%20the%20hedge%20fund%20Crypto%20Lotus%2C%20which%20he%20said%20could%20borrow%20%24100%20million%20from%20FTX%2C%20far%20less%20than%20Alameda's%20line%20of%20credit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20contracts%20Sassoon%20showed%20at%20the%20trial%2C%20companies%20with%20lines%20of%20credit%20needed%20to%20keep%20collateral%20for%20their%20withdrawals%20on%20the%20FTX%20exchange%2C%20so%20that%20their%20assets%20could%20be%20liquidated%20if%20a%20leveraged%20trade%20went%20badly.%20The%20only%20company%20that%20could%20take%20its%20money%20elsewhere%20was%20Alameda.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20most%20damningly%2C%20Sassoon%20brought%20up%20an%20entry%20from%20FTX's%20database%20with%20information%20about%20Alameda's%20main%20account%20on%20the%20exchange.%20I