irman%201st%20Class%20Vaughn%20Weber%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20Russian%20and%20Ukrainian%20militaries%20have%20made%20extensive%20use%20of%20electronic-warfare%20capabilities.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EBoth%20sides%20have%20used%20EW%20to%20interfere%20with%20the%20other's%20communications%20and%20drones%2C%20among%20other%20tasks.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20military%20is%20watching%20that%20unfold%20and%20intensifying%20efforts%20to%20improve%20its%20own%20EW%20capabilities.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EElectronic%20warfare%20has%20become%20a%20major%20factor%20in%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20with%20each%20side%20using%20it%20to%20jam%20the%20other's%20radios%20and%20radars%20and%20to%20knock%20their%20drones%20out%20of%20the%20sky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20value%20of%20electronic-warfare%20capabilities%20is%20not%20a%20new%20lesson%2C%20but%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20has%20shown%20how%20quickly%20those%20capabilities%2C%20and%20means%20of%20countering%20them%2C%20have%20evolved.%20That's%20why%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20is%20eager%20to%20deploy%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20electronic-warfare%20aircraft%20and%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%2C%20the%20Air%20Force%20received%20its%20first%20test%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airandspaceforces.com%2Ffirst-ec-37-delivered-for-testing%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEC-37B%3C%2Fa%3E%20Compass%20Call.%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airandspaceforces.com%2Fweapons-platforms%2Fec-37b%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGulfstream%20G550%3C%2Fa%3E%20business%20jet%20modified%20to%20conduct%20electronic-warfare%20operations%2C%20the%20EC-37%20will%20replace%20the%20aging%20EC-130%2C%20which%20is%20a%20modified%20C-130%20cargo%20plane%20that%20dates%20back%20to%20the%20mid-1970s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22868%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22EC-130H%20EC-37B%20Compass%20Call%20electronic%20warfare%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653fabd196f7540cd0691bec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22434%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEC-130H%20and%20an%20EC-37B%20electronic-warfare%20aircraft.%3Cp%3EL3Harris%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bbottom%20line%20is%20we%20need%20it%20to%20enable%20our%20ships%20and%20aircraft%20to%20get%20closer%20by%20electromagnetic%20protection%20and%20%5Bby%5D%20electronic%20attack%20make%20it%20more%20di%EF%AC%83cult%20for%20adversary%20ships%20and%20aircraft%20to%20operate%20across%26quot%3B%20the%20electromagnetic%20spectrum%2C%20Gen.%20Mark%20Kelly%2C%20commander%20of%20Air%20Combat%20Command%2C%20which%20organizes%2C%20trains%2C%20and%20equips%20US%20Air%20Force%20units%2C%20told%20reporters%20at%20the%20Air%20and%20Space%20Forces%20Association%20conference%20in%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMilitaries%20have%20been%20investing%20in%20the%20secretive%20world%20of%20electronic%20warfare%20since%20World%20War%20II.%20The%20US%20Air%20Force%20uses%20electronic%20warfare%20as%20an%20umbrella%20term%20that%20includes%20electronic%20attack%20(such%20as%20jamming%20enemy%20radios%20or%20anti-radiation%20missiles%20to%20destroy%20enemy%20radar)%2C%20electronic-warfare%20support%20to%20locate%20and%20identify%20enemy%20transmitters%2C%20and%20electromagnetic%20protection%20against%20an%20enemy's%20electronic%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20air%20campaigns%20of%20the%20Vietnam%20and%20Arab-Israeli%20wars%2C%20jamming%20and%20anti-jamming%20of%20air-defense%20radars%20and%20anti-aircraft%20weapons%20played%20a%20major%20role%2C%20but%20during%20the%20fighting%20in%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%94%20on%20land%20and%20in%20the%20air%20%E2%80%94%20electronic%20warfare%20has%20become%20as%20powerful%20as%20tanks%20and%20jets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Vehicles%20with%20tall%20poles%20attached%20to%20them.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64a2e6639fab2b00184af038%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Russian%20R-330Zh%20Zhitel%20electronic-warfare%20station%20in%20an%20exercise%20in%20July%202018.%3Cp%3EDenis%20Abramov%2FRussian%20Defense%20Ministry%20via%20Mil.ru%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20and%20Russia%20constantly%20try%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-electronic-warfare-tactics-changing-on-frontlines-in-ukraine-2023-10%5C%22%3Ejam%20each%20other's%20radio%20communications%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-electronic-warfare-interfering-with-ukrainian-radios-bombs-2023-7%5C%22%3Edisrupt%20or%20spoof%20GPS%20signals%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20guide%20smart%20artillery%20shells.%20To%20stop%20the%20armadas%20of%20small%20reconnaissance%20and%20attack%20drones%20that%20constantly%20orbit%20the%20battlefield%2C%20it's%20cheaper%20to%20disrupt%20their%20command%20links%2C%20which%20causes%20them%20to%20crash%2C%20than%20it%20is%20to%20use%20scarce%20air-defense%20munitions%20to%20shoot%20them%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20have%20capability%20that's%20EW%20resistant%2C%20and%20you%20need%20to%20have%20offensive%20EW%20capability%20that's%20configurable%2C%20because%20the%20enemy's%20going%20to%20make%20advancements%2C%26quot%3B%20Gen.%20James%20Rainey%2C%20head%20of%20US%20Army%20Futures%20Command%2C%20told%20reporters%20at%20the%20Association%20of%20the%20United%20States%20Army's%20annual%20conference%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Army%20has%20several%20projects%20underway%20to%20upgrade%20its%20electronic-warfare%20capabilities%20and%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-russia-war-us-army-urgently-working-on-electronic-warfare-2023-8%5C%22%3Eadded%20%26quot%3Burgency%26quot%3B%20to%20those%20efforts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Doug%20Bush%2C%20the%20Army's%20acquisition%20chief%2C%20told%20reporters%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Army%20is%20%26quot%3Bfundamentally%20reinvesting%20in%20rebuilding%20our%20tactical%20electronic-warfare%20capability%20after%20that%20largely%20left%20the%20force%20over%20the%20last%2020%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Bush%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Army%20soldiers%20electronic%20warfare%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653fd01e356802a56be7786c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Army%20electronic-warfare%20specialists%20set%20up%20portable%20jamming%20packs%20at%20Fort%20Bliss%20in%20Texas%20in%20December%202018.%3Cp%3EStaff%20Sgt.%20Felicia%20Jagdatt%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20Air%20Force%2C%20the%20role%20of%20the%20new%20EC-37B%20will%20not%20be%20%26quot%3Boverly%20different%20than%20what%20the%20EC-130's%20been%20doing%20for%20air%20superiority%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelly%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20just%20need%20it%20to%20move%20around%20a%20large%20expanse%20of%20airspace%2C%20and%20we'll%20be%20using%20advanced%20techniques%20to%20make%20sure%20we%20can%20operate%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20electromagnetic%20spectrum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20aircraft%20itself%20is%20an%20improvement%20over%20its%20predecessor.%20The%20EC-37B%20is%20%26quot%3Bfaster%2C%20more%20economical%2C%20capable%20of%20higher%20altitude%20operations%2C%20and%20more%20survivable%20than%20the%20EC-130H%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20its%20upgrades%20will%20allow%20it%20to%20conduct%20jamming%20and%20electronic%20attack%20from%20longer%20ranges%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airandspaceforces.com%2Fweapons-platforms%2Fec-37b%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAir%20and%20Space%20Forces%20magazine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElectronic%20warfare%20is%20also%20one%20of%20the%20most%20delicate%20operations%20that%20militaries%20conduct%2C%20requiring%20precision%20and%20coordination%20to%20ensure%20enemy%20forces%20are%20affected%20and%20friendly%20forces%20are%20not.%20For%20example%2C%20Russian%20jamming%20of%20Ukrainian%20air-defense%20radars%20early%20in%20the%20war%20also%20end%20up%20jamming%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-ew-campaign-in-ukraine-undermined-by-electronic-fratricide-2022-11%5C%22%3ERussian%20Army's%20radio%20communications%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENaturally%2C%20the%20Air%20Force%20wants%20to%20extensively%20test%20the%20E-37B%20before%20deploying%20it.%20The%20service%20is%20confident%20in%20the%20airplane%20but%20needs%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20mission%20systems%20aboard%20it%20will%20function%20as%20needed%20and%20when%20needed%2C%20Kelly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Air%20Force%20EC-130H%20Compass%20Call%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653fd01e356802a56be7786b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20Air%20Force%20EC-130H%20at%20Davis-Monthan%20Air%20Force%20Base%20in%20August%202021.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%2FSenior%20Airman%20Alex%20Miller%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20all%20about%20the%20mission%20systems%2C%20and%20when%20we%20dial%20up%20the%20jamming%20power%20or%20ask%20for%20a%20specific%20waveform%2C%20that%20waveform%20needs%20to%20come%20out%20at%20exactly%20the%20amount%20of%20ramp%20and%20power%20and%20frequency%20we%20asked%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelly%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20ask%20for%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20jamming%2C%20that's%20what%20you%20get.%20When%20you%20turn%20it%20off%2C%20it%20turns%20off.%20We%20aren't%20straining%20the%20environmental%20system%20of%20the%20airplane%2C%20so%20on%20and%20so%20forth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20EC-37B%20has%20been%20in%20the%20works%20for%20some%20time%2C%20but%20Air%20Force%20is%20also%20looking%20to%20unmanned%20aircraft%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-air-force-collaborative-combat-aircraft-drones-fighter-jets-2023-5%5C%22%3Eto%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-air-force-collaborative-combat-aircraft-drones-fighter-jets-2023-5%5C%22%3Eadd%20mass%20and%20capability%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20its%20fleet.%20The%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airandspaceforces.com%2Fusaf-5-8-billion-ccas-five-years-spectral-warfare%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECollaborative%20Combat%20Aircraft%3C%2Fa%3E%20program%20aims%20to%20develop%20robot%20wingmen%20for%20current%20US%20warplanes%20and%20for%20the%20Air%20Force's%20Next-Generation%20Air%20Dominance%20project%2C%20which%20aims%20to%20produce%20a%20sixth-generation%20fighter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20priority%20missions%20for%20the%20CCAs%20at%20a%20conference%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20Kelly%20pointed%20to%20jamming%2C%20alongside%20sensing%2C%20signals%20intelligence%2C%20and%20similar%20missions.%20The%20%26quot%3Bhurdle%26quot%3B%20will%20be%20determining%20the%20size%2C%20weight%2C%20and%20power%20available%20to%20support%20those%20payloads%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20I%20think%20we'll%20iterate%20from%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMichael%20Peck%20is%20a%20defense%20writer%20whose%20work%20has%20appeared%20in%20Forbes%2C%20Defense%20News%2C%20Foreign%20Policy%20magazine%2C%20and%20other%20publications.%20He%20holds%20a%20master's%20in%20political%20science.%20Follow%20him%20on%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twitter.com%2F%40mipeck1%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22a48008f66dd60e4ae3cb2319a8aa10eb%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twitter.com%2F%40mipeck1%5