blank%5C%22%3Estruck%20down%20Biden's%20first%20plan%20for%20broad%20debt%20relief%3C%2Fa%3E%20using%20the%20HEROES%20Act%20of%202003%2C%20which%20allowed%20the%20education%20secretary%20to%20waive%20or%20modify%20student-loan%20balances%20in%20connection%20with%20a%20national%20emergency%2C%20like%20COVID-19.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20ruled%20Biden%20did%20not%20have%20the%20authority%20to%20cancel%20student%20debt%20broadly%20using%20that%20law.%20The%20Higher%20Education%20Act%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20does%20not%20require%20the%20reliance%20of%20a%20national%20emergency%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20does%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-long-will-take-cancel-student-debt-higher-education-act-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erequire%20the%20administration%20go%20through%20negotiated%20rulemaking%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20involves%20a%20series%20of%20negotiation%20sessions%20with%20higher%20education%20stakeholders%20and%20borrowers%20to%20craft%20a%20final%20regulation%20for%20the%20new%20debt%20relief%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMonday's%20announcement%20was%20the%20latest%20step%20in%20that%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20draft%20proposals%20would%20build%20on%20the%20historic%20%24127%20billion%20in%20loan%20forgiveness%20the%20Biden-Harris%20administration%20has%20already%20approved%20for%20nearly%203.6%20million%20borrowers%2C%26quot%3B%20Education%20Secretary%20Miguel%20Cardona%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20fighting%20to%20ensure%20that%20student%20debt%20does%20not%20stand%20in%20the%20way%20of%20opportunity%20or%20prevent%20borrowers%20from%20realizing%20the%20benefits%20of%20their%20higher%20education.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20draft%20regulatory%20text%20identified%20four%20groups%20of%20borrowers%20the%20department%20is%20seeking%20to%20prioritize%20for%20debt%20relief%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20have%20outstanding%20balances%20that%20exceed%20what%20they%20originally%20borrowed%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20have%20loans%20that%20entered%20repayment%2025%20or%20more%20years%20ago%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20took%20out%20loans%20to%20attend%20programs%20that%20left%20them%20with%20too%20much%20debt%20compared%20to%20post-grad%20earnings%2C%20along%20with%20those%20who%20went%20to%20schools%20with%20%26quot%3Bunacceptably%20high%26quot%3B%20default%20rates%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20those%20who%20are%20eligible%20for%20forgiveness%20under%20repayment%20plans%20like%20income-driven%20repayment%20and%20Public%20Service%20Loan%20Forgiveness%20but%20have%20not%20yet%20applied%20for%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20agree%20that%20there%20are%20struggling%20borrowers%20who%20are%20not%20yet%20reached%20by%20existing%20loan%20forgiveness%20programs%20and%20repayment%20options%2C%26quot%3B%20Under%20Secretary%20of%20Education%20James%20Kvaal%20told%20reporters%20on%20a%20press%20call.%20%26quot%3BAdditional%20discussion%20and%20evidence%20is%20needed%20to%20define%20those%20groups%20and%20any%20possible%20policy%20solutions%20with%20more%20precision.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20senior%20department%20official%20also%20told%20reporters%20that%20the%20amount%20of%20student%20debt%20canceled%20could%20vary%20by%20each%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20groups%20have%20not%20changed%20from%20the%20initial%20issue%20paper%20the%20department%20released%20last%20month%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-will-be-included-in-new-broad-student-loan-forgiveness-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoutlined%20the%20groups%20of%20borrowers%20it%20wanted%20negotiators%20to%20focus%20on%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20at%20this%20time%20it%20excludes%20a%20fifth%20category%3A%20those%20who%20are%20experiencing%20financial%20hardship%20%26quot%3Bin%20ways%20that%20the%20current%20student%20loan%20sys