.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67261127.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67261127.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Loss%20Of%20Trust%20Between%20Married%20Couple%20Not%20Mental%20Cruelty%3A%20Delhi%20High%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ETrivial%20irritations%20and%20loss%20of%20trust%20between%20married%20couples%20cannot%20be%20confused%20with%20mental%20cruelty%2C%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20said%20on%20Monday%20as%20it%20refused%20to%20uphold%20a%20lower%20court%20order%20granting%20divorce%20on%20a%20husband's%20plea%20against%20his%20wife.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20husband%20sought%20divorce%20on%20account%20of%20mental%20cruelty%20by%20the%20wife%2C%20alleging%20that%20she%20was%20not%20interested%20in%20living%20with%20him%20in%20the%20matrimonial%20home%20and%20wanted%20him%20to%20live%20with%20her%20at%20her%20parental%20home%20as%20%26quot%3Bghar%20jamai%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETheir%20marriage%20was%20solemnised%20in%201996%20according%20to%20Hindu%20rites%20and%20customs%20and%20they%20were%20blessed%20with%20a%20baby%20girl%20in%201998.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20man%20had%20claimed%20that%20his%20wife%20used%20to%20desert%20him%20on%20one%20pretext%20or%20the%20other%2C%20was%20only%20interested%20in%20running%20her%20coaching%20centre%20and%20even%20denied%20him%20sex.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDealing%20with%20the%20wife's%20appeal%2C%20a%20bench%20headed%20by%20Justice%20Sanjeev%20Sachdeva%20said%20although%20denial%20of%20sex%20can%20be%20considered%20a%20form%20of%20mental%20cruelty%20when%20it%20is%20persistent%2C%20intentional%20and%20for%20a%20considerable%20period%20of%20time%2C%20the%20court%20needs%20to%20%26quot%3Bover-circumspect%26quot%3B%20while%20dealing%20with%20such%20a%20sensitive%20and%20delicate%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESuch%20allegations%2C%20the%20court%20said%2C%20could%20not%20be%20proved%20merely%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20vague%20and%20unspecific%20averments%2C%20particularly%20when%20the%20marriage%20was%20also%20duly%20consummated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20held%20that%20the%20husband%20had%20failed%20to%20prove%20any%20mental%20cruelty%20on%20him%20and%20the%20present%20instance%20was%20%26quot%3Bsimply%20a%20case%20of%20normal%20wear%20and%20tear%20of%20the%20matrimonial%20bond%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20evidence%20indicated%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bdiscord%20was%20between%20the%20wife%20and%20her%20mother-in-law%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20nothing%20to%20affirmatively%20suggest%20that%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20wife%20was%20of%20such%20a%20nature%20that%20it%20was%20no%20longer%20possible%20for%20her%20husband%20to%20stay%20with%20her.%20The%20trivial%20irritations%20and%20loss%20of%20trust%20cannot%20be%20confused%20with%20mental%20cruelty%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20bench%2C%20also%20comprising%20Justice%20Manoj%20Jain.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20said%20the%20mere%20fact%20that%20the%20woman%20had%20approached%20police%20with%20a%20criminal%20complaint%2C%20resulting%20in%20an%20FIR%20against%20her%20husband%20who%20was%20eventually%20granted%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20doubt%20in%20the%20matter%2C%20would%20not%20amount%20to%20cruelty.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThus%2C%20the%20picture%20which%20emerges%20out%20is%20very%20clear.%20There%20was%20loss%20of%20trust%2C%20faith%20and%20affection%20between%20the%20parties%20but%20despite%20that%2C%20they%20both%20were%20trying%20hard%20to%20save%20the%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMerely%20because%20the%20wife%20had%20knocked%20the%20doors%20of%20the%20court%20for%20redressal%20of%20her%20grievance%2C%20just%20like%20her%20husband%20also%20did%2C%20cannot%20tantamount%20to%20infliction%20of%20cruelty.%20The%20evidence%20led%20by%20the%20husband%2C%20when%20tested%20on%20the%20yardstick%20of%20preponderance%20of%20probabilities%2C%20does%20not%20seem%20compelling%20enough%20to%20prove%20cruelty%20on%20the%20part%20of%20his%20wife%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20further%20rejected%20the%20husband's%20plea%20to%20grant%20him%20divorce%20on%20account%20of%20an%20%26quot%3Birretrievable%20breakdown%26quot%3B%20of%20their%20marriage%20and%20said%20such%20power%20vests%20only%20with%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20cannot%20be%20sought%20by%20any%20of%20the%20parties%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20power%20to%20grant%20divorce%20on%20the%20ground%20of%20irretrievable%20breakdown%20of%20marriage%20is%20exercised%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20under%20Article%20142%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20to%20do%20complete%20justice%20to%20both%20the%20parties.%20Such%20a%20power%20is%20not%20vested%20in%20the%20high%20courts%2C%20leave%20alone%20the%20family%20courts%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20an%20upshot%20of%20our%20foregoing%20discussion%2C%20we%20hold%20that%20the%20impugned%20judgment%20dated%20September%207%2C%202019%20is%20not%20sustainable.%20The%20appeal%20is%2C%20resultantly%2C%20allowed%20and%20as%20a%20necessary%20corollary%2C%20the%20divorce%20petition%20filed%20by%20the%20husband%20stands%20dismissed%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20ordered.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698680280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2016-02%2Fdelhi-high-court_650x400_41454944412.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ftrivial-irritations-loss-of-trust-between-married-couple-not-mental-cruelty-delhi-hc-4528945%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Trivial%20irritations%20and%20loss%20of%20trust%20between%20married%20couples%20cannot%20be%20confused%20with%20mental%20cruelty%2C%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20said%20on%20Monday%20as%2