n%2C%20and%20perseverance.%20Suffice%20it%20to%20say%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20impossible%20to%20capture%20Anne%E2%80%99s%20work%20entirely%20given%20its%20immense%20scope%20and%20breadth.%20However%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20possible%20to%20capture%20some%20of%20its%20fascinating%20highlights%20with%20assistance%20from%20wildlife%20historian%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F233080%2Ftigress-khairi-simlipal-odisha-ifs-officer-saroj-raj-choudhury-documentary-pugmark-method-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERaza%20Kazmi%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20knew%20Anne%20and%20her%20family%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20900px)%20100vw%2C%20900px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Project-Tiger-1698674434.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Anne%20Wright%20with%20Indira%20Gandhi%20and%20others%20presenting%20%E2%80%98Tiger%20in%20the%20Sun%E2%80%99%20to%20raise%20funds%20for%20Project%20Tiger%20in%20New%20Delhi%20in%201975.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Project-Tiger-1698674434.jpg%20900w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Project-Tiger-1698674434-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Project-Tiger-1698674434-500x281.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Project-Tiger-1698674434-768x432.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Project-Tiger-1698674434-150x84.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-333236%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22506%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAnne%20Wright%20(second%20from%20left)%20with%20Indira%20Gandhi%20and%20others%20presenting%20%E2%80%98Tiger%20in%20the%20Sun%E2%80%99%20to%20raise%20funds%20for%20Project%20Tiger%20in%20New%20Delhi%20in%201975.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20woman%20of%20the%20forests%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%201929%2C%20Anne%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20her%20childhood%20in%20the%20forests%20of%20what%20are%20today%20the%20tiger%20reserves%20of%20Melghat%20and%20Kanha%20in%20the%20erstwhile%20Central%20Provinces.%20After%20all%20her%20father%20was%20an%20officer%20with%20the%20erstwhile%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F254803%2Findia-history-freedom-struggle-michael-john-carritt-ics-officer-hero-bengal-communist-party-british-rule-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndian%20Civil%20Service%20(ICS)%3C%2Fa%3E%20serving%20in%20the%20Central%20Provinces%20that%20include%20parts%20of%20present-day%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Chhattisgarh%20and%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsanctuarynaturefoundation.org%2Faward%2Fanne-wright%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethis%202013%20tribute%3C%2Fa%3E%20written%20by%20the%20Sanctuary%20Nature%20Foundation%2C%20%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20child%2C%20she%20%5BAnne%20Wright%5D%20would%20search%20for%20scorpions%2C%20follow%20tigers%E2%80%99%20pugmarks%20on%20golf%20courses%20and%20watch%20panthers%20leap%20across%20the%20parapets%20of%20Amravati%E2%80%99s%20rugged%20Gawilgarh%20Fort.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20her%20fascination%20with%20wildlife%2C%20Anne%20lived%20at%20a%20time%20when%20big%20game%20hunting%20was%20still%20commonplace.%20Speaking%20to%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20wildlife%20historian%20Raza%20Kazmi%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CAnne%20Wright%20and%20her%20husband%20Robert%20Hamilton%20Wright%20(Bob%20Wright%20to%20those%20who%20knew%20him)%20had%20begun%20coming%20to%20the%20forests%20of%20Palamau%20(in%20present-day%20Jharkhand)%20from%20about%201949%E2%80%9350%20onwards.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20those%20days%2C%20as%20was%20the%20norm%2C%20most%20of%20Bob%E2%80%99s%20friends%20liked%20doing%20a%20bit%20of%20hunting%20and%20the%20forests%20of%20Palamau%20were%20a%20favourite%20among%20hunters%20based%20in%20Calcutta%20(Kolkata).%20Moreover%2C%20the%20British%20conglomerate%20Bob%20was%20working%20for%20at%20the%20time%20in%20Calcutta%2C%20Andrew%20Yule%20%26amp%3B%20Co%20Ltd%2C%20had%20one%20of%20its%20major%20supply%20sites%20in%20Palamau.%20Anne%2C%20who%20had%20started%20living%20with%20her%20husband%20in%20Calcutta%20by%20then%2C%20would%20come%20along%20with%20Bob%20often.%20She%20never%20hunted%20but%20used%20these%20visits%20to%20get%20to%20know%20these%20forests%20of%20Palamau%20quite%20intimately%20over%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Raza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnne%20always%20carried%20a%20deep%20love%20and%20admiration%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20forests%20and%20wildlife.%20But%20it%20was%20only%20in%20the%20mid-1960s%20when%20conservation%20really%20became%20a%20part%20of%20her%20life%20following%20regular%20visits%20to%20the%20jungles%20of%20present-day%20Bihar%20and%20Jharkhand%2C%20and%20particularly%20after%20the%20onset%20of%20the%20Great%20Bihar%20Famine%20of%201966%E2%80%9367%20which%20took%20a%20massive%20toll%20on%20the%20local%20wildlife.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Final-Feature-Image-05-1698675652.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Anne%20Wright%20shared%20an%20abiding%20love%20and%20passion%20for%20India's%20wildlife.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Final-Feature-Image-05-1698675652.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Final-Feature-Image-05-1698675652-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Final-Feature-Image-05-1698675652-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Final-Feature-Image-05-1698675652-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Final-Feature-Image-05-1698675652-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-333247%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAnne%20Wright%20shared%20an%20abiding%20love%20and%20passion%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20wildlife.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESaving%20Palamau%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EFrom%201949%E2%80%9350%20onwards%2C%20Anne%E2%80%99s%20family%20would%20regularly%20visit%20the%20forests%20of%20Palamau%20(known%20for%20its%20tigers)%20located%20in%20the%20Latehar%20district%20(formerly%20part%20of%20Palamau%20district)%20of%20present-day%20Jharkhand.%20According%20to%20Raza%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20Anne%20had%20always%20been%20a%20forest%20and%20wildlife%20enthusiast%2C%20given%20her%20childhood%20spent%20in%20the%20wilds%20of%20Central%20Provinces%20with%20her%20father%2C%20she%20told%20me%20that%20it%20was%20the%20naturalist%20EP%20Gee%20(credited%20with%20the%20discovery%20of%20the%20Gee%20golden%20langur)%20who%20was%20instrumental%20in%20guiding%20her%20towards%20a%20life%20of%20wildlife%20conservation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBy%20the%201960s%2C%20Anne%20had%20begun%20noticing%20a%20decline%20in%20wildlife%20in%20Palamau%20and%20began%20actively%20trying%20to%20do%20her%20bit%20to%20address%20it.%20Over%20the%20years%20she%20had%20cultivated%20friendship%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20committed%20and%20like-minded%20forest%20officers%20of%20undivided%20Bihar%20among%20whom%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F300043%2Fforgotten-forest-officer-sp-shahi-behind-indias-only-wolf-sanctuary-mahuadanr-jharkhand%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESP%20Shahi%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20the%20most%20prominent.%20When%20the%201967%20Great%20Famine%20of%20Bihar%20hit%20Palamau%2C%20Anne%20dropped%20everything%2C%20collected%20funds%20from%20various%20donors%2C%20and%20came%20to%20Palamau%20to%20do%20her%20bit%20to%20help%20out%20both%20the%20affected%20communities%20and%20the%20wildlife%20that%20was%20perishing%20during%20this%20crisis%20as%20well%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnne%20spent%20months%20in%20remote%20forest%20bungalows%20in%20the%20forests%20of%20Palamau%20and%20worked%20tirelessly%20to%20organise%20communal%20meals%20and%20water%20supply%20for%20the%20people.%20She%20also%20developed%20waterholes%20for%20the%20bewildered%20wildlife%20that%20was%20coming%20out%20of%20the%20forests%20in%20search%20of%20water%20and%20getting%20killed%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Bihar-Famine-1698674937.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22During%20the%20Great%20Bihar%20Famine%2C%20Anne%20and%20her%20team%20served%20local%20communities%20and%20wildlife.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Bihar-Famine-1698674937.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Bihar-Famine-1698674937-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Bihar-Famine-1698674937-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Bihar-Famine-1698674937-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Bihar-Famine-1698674937-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-333241%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EDuring%20the%20Great%20Bihar%20Famine%2C%20Anne%20and%20her%20team%20served%20local%20communities%20and%20wildlife.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHer%20fortitude%20and%20toughness%20earned%20her%20the%20respect%20of%20the%20forest%20bureaucracy%20and%20her%20kindness%20touched%20many%20of%20the%20local%20Adivasi%20communities%20who%20in%20most%20cases%20completely%20relied%20on%20the%20food%2C%20water%20and%20medicines%20provided%20by%20Anne%E2%80%99s%20team%20for%20relief%2C%E2%80%9D%20notes%20Raza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20she%20had%20begun%20realising%20that%20the%20forests%20and%20wildlife%20of%20Palamau%20could%20not%20be%20protected%20in%20the%20long%20run%20with%20just%20individual%20efforts.%20She%20also%20knew%20that%20it%20would%20need%20an%20institutional%20support%20system%20both%20within%20and%20outside%20the%20government%20to%20make%20meaningful%20long-term%20change.%20According%20to%20Raza%2C%20those%20were%20the%20days%20when%20funds%20were%20severely%20lacking%20for%20the%20forest%20department%20with%20almost%20nothing%20for%20the%20management%20of%20wildlife%20or%20their%20protection.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20she%20started%20working%20on%20both%20fronts%20for%20Palamau.%20She%20worked%20tirelessly%20in%20convincing%20and%20lobbying%20the%20political%20class%20at%20the%20State%20and%20Union%20government%20levels%20on%20the%20importance%20of%20Palamau%20and%20the%20preservation%20of%20its%20wildlife.%20Simultaneously%2C%20she%20helped%20set%20up%20the%20India%20chapter%20of%20the%20World%20Wildlife%20Fund%20(WWF)%20in%201969%20and%20ensured%20that%20Palamau%20was%20among%20the%20first%20forests%20that%20the%20organisation%20focused%20its%20energies%20upon%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Raza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%20that%20she%20began%20helping%20the%20forest%20department%20itself%20with%20making%20a%20case%20for%20this%20forest%20from%20within%20the%20system.%20Anne%20brought%20top%20ecologists%20and%20experts%20from%20IUCN%20(International%20Union%20for%20Conservation%20of%20Nature)%20and%20WWF%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20Dr%20Colin%20Holloway%20%E2%80%94%20to%20visit%20Palamau.%20She%20got%20them%20to%20train%20the%20officers%20and%20staff%20there%20in%20the%20latest%20techniques%20of%20wildlife%20management%2C%20while%20also%20helping%20them%20draw%20a%20wildlife%20management%20plan%20for%20this%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20fact%2C%20Anne%20spent%20long%20hours%20with%20Dr%20Holloway%2C%20SP%20Shahi%20and%20other%20forest%20officers%20like%20RP%20Singh%20and%20JP%20Sinha%20in%20devising%20the%20first%20comprehensive%20wildlife%20management%20plan%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20history%20for%20a%20%E2%80%98Game%20Sanctuary%E2%80%99.%20Such%20a%20plan%20was%20almost%20unheard%20of%20in%20the%20pre-Wildlife%20(Protection)%20Act%20era%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20Wildlife%20(Protection)%20Act%2C%201972%2C%20a%20wildlife-rich%20forest%20was%20sometimes%20notified%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98Game%20Sanctuary%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Anne%20also%20helped%20in%20advising%20the%20forest%20officers%20in%20Palamau%20with%20creating%20the%20necessary%20infrastructure%20for%20the%20management%20and%20conservation%20of%20wildlife%20in%20the%20region%2C%20and%20also%20ensuring%20that%20the%20funds-starved%20offices%20of%20Palamau%20Forest%20Division%20(under%20which%20these%20forests%20lay)%20got%20funding%20from%20non-governmental%20sources%20and%20donors%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20biggest%20of%20which%20was%20WWF%20where%20she%20had%20considerable%20say%20and%20influence%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Raza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20she%20was%20doing%20all%20this%20groundwork%20while%20being%20in%20the%20field%20at%20Palamau%2C%20she%20was%20simultaneously%20pushing%20for%20Palamau%E2%80%99s%20protection%20at%20the%20Union%20Government%20level%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFrom%20Palamau%20to%20Project%20Tiger%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EHer%20work%2C%20however%2C%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20just%20restricted%20to%20the%20forests%20of%20Palamau.%20She%20was%20also%20investigating%20the%20growing%20big%20cat%20skin%20trade%20in%20Kolkata.%20In%201970%2C%20she%20wrote%20an%20article%20published%20in%20The%20Statesman%20which%20describes%20in%20harrowing%20detail%20the%20illegal%20sale%20of%20tiger%20and%20leopard%20skins%20in%20Kolkata.%20The%20article%20was%20republished%20in%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20(NYT)%2C%20causing%20a%20global%20storm.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20Raza%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20article%20was%20debated%20heavily%20in%20the%20Indian%20Parliament%2C%20and%20it%20isn%E2%80%99t%20an%20exaggeration%20to%20say%20that%20this%20article%2C%20along%20with%20the%20damning%20photographs%20on%20the%20scale%20of%20tiger%20hunting%20especially%20for%20skin%20trade%2C%20convinced%20the%20then%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20to%20ban%20tiger%20hunting%20the%20very%20same%20year%20(1970).%20That%20was%20the%20power%20of%20her%20pen.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Tiger-Skin-Trade-1698675174.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Anne%20Wright%20diligently%20documented%20the%20big%20cat%20skin%20trade.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Tiger-Skin-Trade-1698675174.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Tiger-Skin-Trade-1698675174-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Tiger-Skin-Trade-1698675174-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Tiger-Skin-Trade-1698675174-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Tiger-Skin-Trade-1698675174-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-333242%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAnne%20Wright%20diligently%20documented%20the%20big%20cat%20skin%20trade.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20didn%E2%80%99t%20stop%20there.%20The%20global%20outcry%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20NYT%20republishing%20her%20article%20led%20to%20an%20outpouring%20of%20support%20for%20tiger%20conservation%20in%20India%20in%20terms%20of%20funds%2C%20resources%20and%20expertise.%20It%20culminated%20in%20the%20landmark%20%E2%80%98Operation%20Tiger%E2%80%99%20that%20began%20in%201971%20and%20eventually%20transformed%20into%20Project%20Tiger.%20Following%20the%20start%20of%20Operation%20Tiger%2C%20a%20task%20force%20of%20forest%20officers%2C%20conservationists%20and%20other%20eminent%20personalities%20was%20set%20up%20by%20the%20Indian%20government.%20Often%20known%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98First%20Tiger%20Task%20Force%E2%80%99%2C%20it%20was%20tasked%20with%20identifying%20areas%20for%20central%20funding%20and%20guidance%20for%20tiger%20conservation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20such%20task%20force%20was%20formed%20in%202005%20following%20reports%20in%20the%20media%20on%20the%20sudden%20disappearance%20of%20tigers%20from%20the%20Sariska%20Wildlife%20Reserve.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnne%20was%20the%20only%20female%20member%20of%20this%20task%20force%2C%20and%20this%20is%20where%20she%20spoke%20vociferously%20about%20the%20inclusion%20of%20Palamau%E2%80%99s%20forests%20as%20one%20such%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20she%20had%20done%20so%20much%20groundwork%20in%20coordination%20with%20the%20concerned%20forest%20officers%20there%20now%20became%20a%20very%20important%20factor%20in%20helping%20her%20case%20for%20Palamau.%20Thus%2C%20eventually%20when%20the%20Task%20Force%20submitted%20its%20final%20report%20titled%20%E2%80%98Project%20Tiger%E2%80%99%2C%20Palamau%20was%20among%20the%20eight%20forests%20identified%20in%20the%20final%20report%20for%20central%20funding%20and%20handholding.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20report%20then%20ushered%20in%20the%20Project%20Tiger%20scheme%2C%20and%20Palamau%20became%20one%20of%20the%20inaugural%20nine%20tiger%20reserves.%20Anne%20continued%20being%20involved%20in%20helping%20the%20tiger%20reserve%20management%20all%20through%20the%201970s%2C%20and%20by%20the%20early%201980s%2C%20Palamau%20was%20being%20ranked%20as%20one%20of%20the%20best-managed%20tiger%20reserves%20in%20the%20entire%20country.%20Besides%20Palamau%2C%20she%20also%20supported%20the%20cause%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F233080%2Ftigress-khairi-simlipal-odisha-ifs-officer-saroj-raj-choudhury-documentary-pugmark-method-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESimilipal%20in%20Odisha%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20also%20became%20a%20tiger%20reserve%2C%E2%80%9D%20notes%20Raza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGoing%20further%2C%20she%20was%20also%20appointed%20by%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20help%20draft%20the%20landmark%20Wildlife%20(Protection)%20Act%2C%201972.%20Interestingly%2C%20according%20to%20Raza%2C%20she%20sourced%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20Kenyan%20Wildlife%20Act%20%5Bfrom%20the%20Kenyan%20national%20polo%20team%20that%20had%20visited%20Kolkata%20to%20play%20a%20couple%20of%20matches%5D%2C%20which%20alongside%20the%20Bombay%20Animals%20Act%20was%20among%20the%20two%20key%20legislative%20influences%20in%20the%20drafting%20of%20the%20final%20Wildlife%20(Protection)%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Power-of-the-Pen-1698675275.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Anne%20Wright%20used%20the%20power%20of%20her%20pen%20to%20protect%20India's%20wildlife.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Power-of-the-Pen-1698675275.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Power-of-the-Pen-1698675275-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Power-of-the-Pen-1698675275-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Power-of-the-Pen-1698675275-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Power-of-the-Pen-1698675275-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-333243%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAnne%20Wright%20used%20the%20power%20of%20her%20pen%20to%20protect%20India%E2%80%99s%20wildlife.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHelping%20establish%20other%20Protected%20Areas%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWithout%20Anne%2C%20there%20would%20have%20been%20no%20Dalma%20Wildlife%20Sanctuary%2C%20a%20critical%20elephant%20habitat%20abutting%20Jamshedpur.%20She%20actively%20worked%20with%20the%20highest%20offices%20at%20the%20Union%20and%20State%20government%20levels%20to%20get%20it%20notified%20as%20a%20sanctuary%20in%201976%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Raza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnne%20first%20visited%20Dalma%20soon%20after%20WWF%20came%20to%20India%20(WWF-India%20was%20founded%20in%201969).%20At%20the%20time%2C%20she%20was%20heading%20the%20Eastern%20Branch%20of%20the%20organisation.%20After%20her%20visit%20to%20these%20forests%20that%20lay%20adjacent%20to%20the%20famous%20steel%20city%20of%20Jamshedpur%2C%20she%20wrote%20an%20article%20for%20the%20WWF%20Newsletter%20in%201974%20and%20began%20working%20to%20protect%20these%20forests.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBy%20then%2C%20the%20Wildlife%20(Protection)%20Act%20had%20come%20into%20effect%2C%20and%20she%20lobbied%20hard%20with%20the%20Bihar%20forest%20department%2C%20the%20union%20government%20and%20the%20Tata%20Group%2C%20the%20standout%20private%20corporation%20in%20the%20area%2C%20to%20protect%20the%20forests%20of%20Dalma.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CShe%20ensured%20that%20the%20plight%20of%20Dalma%2C%20its%20elephants%2C%20and%20wildlife%2C%20and%20the%20problem%20of%20unregulated%20customary%20hunting%20that%20was%20rapidly%20depleting%20the%20local%20fauna%20got%20enough%20press%20in%20Calcutta-based%20dailies%20as%20well%20as%20in%20WWF%20Newsletters%20and%20other%20publications.%20Meanwhile%2C%20funds%20for%20building%20basic%20infrastructure%20for%20wildlife%20management%20in%20these%20forests%20were%20arranged%20through%20the%20Tata%20Group%2C%20WWF%2C%20and%20other%20donors.%20Besides%2C%20she%20was%20also%20hard%20at%20work%20convincing%20the%20state%20government%20to%20provide%20financial%20support%20here%20as%20well%2C%E2%80%9D%20notes%20Raza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20she%20worked%20on%20mapping%20the%20best%20quality%20habitats%20that%20could%20be%20notified%20as%20a%20wildlife%20sanctuary%20with%20officers%20like%20SP%20Shahi%20and%20conservationists%20like%20Ashok%20Kumar%2C%20founder%20of%20the%20now%20well-known%20Wildlife%20Trust%20of%20India%20(WTI).%20She%20also%20launched%20a%20massive%20campaign%20to%20popularise%20Dalma%20among%20school%20students%20and%20Tata%20offices%20in%20Jamshedpur%20through%20the%20WWF.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20addition%2C%20she%20lobbied%20hard%20for%20this%20forest%20in%20her%20meetings%20in%20Delhi%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Indian%20Board%20for%20Wildlife%2C%20which%20was%20presided%20over%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi.%20Eventually%2C%20two%20years%20after%20Anne%20first%20wrote%20about%20Dalma%20and%20began%20her%20efforts%20to%20secure%20this%20landscape%2C%20the%20forests%20of%20Dalma%20hills%20were%20notified%20as%20a%20wildlife%20sanctuary%20on%201%20December%201976%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBesides%20the%20Palamau%20Tiger%20Reserve%20and%20Dalma%20Wildlife%20Sanctuary%2C%20Anne%20was%20also%20responsible%20for%20the%20creation%20of%20other%20Protected%20Areas%20like%20the%20Balphakram%20National%20Park%20in%20Meghalaya%20(1986)%20and%20Neora%20Valley%20National%20Park%20in%20West%20Bengal%20(1986).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMoreover%2C%20she%20cared%20deeply%20for%20the%20communities%20around%20the%20forest.%20In%20fact%2C%20her%20progression%20to%20becoming%20someone%20who%20dedicated%20her%20life%20towards%20wildlife%20conservation%20came%20in%20many%20ways%20because%20of%20her%20experience%20serving%20the%20remotest%20forest%20villages%20of%20Palamau%20during%20the%20Great%20Bihar%20Famine%20of%201967.%20Palamau%20was%20one%20of%20the%20epicentres%20of%20this%20famine.%20She%20camped%20for%20weeks%20at%20remote%20spartan%20forest%20bungalows%20like%20Kumandih%20(now%20lost)%20with%20her%20team%20from%20Calcutta%20providing%20relief%20for%20the%20starving%20masses%20by%20putting%20up%20open%20kitchens%2C%20water%20and%20food%20supplies%2C%20medical%20support%2C%20etc%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnne%20served%20on%20the%20Indian%20Board%20for%20Wildlife%20for%2019%20years%2C%20besides%20the%20Wildlife%20Boards%20of%20seven%20states%20from%20Meghalaya%20to%20the%20Andamans.%20She%20also%20established%20the%20Rhino%20Foundation%20and%20supported%20numerous%20organisations%20involved%20in%20the%20conservation%20of%20the%20rhino%20including%20Aaranyak.%20Recognising%20her%20incredible%20service%20to%20wildlife%20conservation%2C%20she%20was%20awarded%20the%20Order%20of%20the%20Golden%20Ark%20in%201979%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98Most%20Excellent%20Order%20of%20the%20British%20Empire%E2%80%99%20(MBE)%20in%201983.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201982%2C%20she%20came%20back%20to%20the%20jungles%20of%20Kanha%2C%20where%20she%20grew%20up%20as%20a%20child%2C%20to%20establish%20Kipling%20%5Bwildlife%5D%20Camp.%20She%20spent%20the%20last%20three%20years%20of%20her%20life%20in%20these%20forests%20with%20her%20daughter%20Belinda%20Wright%2C%20who%20herself%20has%20made%20incredible%20contributions%20to%20tiger%20and%20wildlife%20conservation%20in%20India%2C%20and%20according%20to%20Raza%20remains%20%E2%80%9CAnne%E2%80%99s%20finest%20legacy%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Last-Years-1698675356.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Anne%20Wright%2C%20her%20daughter%20Belinda%20Wright%2C%20and%20the%20wildlife%20historian%20Raza%20Kazmi.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Last-Years-1698675356.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Last-Years-1698675356-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Last-Years-1698675356-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Last-Years-1698675356-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Last-Years-1698675356-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-333244%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAnne%20Wright%2C%20her%20daughter%20Belinda%20Wright%2C%20and%20the%20wildlife%20historian%20Raza%20Kazmi.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ELegacy%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EBesides%20raising%20Belinda%2C%20Anne%20leaves%20behind%20an%20incredible%20legacy%20in%20just%20the%20incredible%20breadth%20and%20depth%20of%20her%20work.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20breadth%20is%20both%20temporal%20as%20she%20played%20an%20active%20role%20in%20the%20conservation%20of%20wildlife%20in%20India%20for%20more%20than%2050%20years%20and%20geographic%20since%20her%20active%20field%20conservation%20work%20spanned%20from%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20to%20the%20remote%20valleys%20of%20Meghalaya%2C%20the%20mangroves%20of%20Sunderbans%2C%20wilds%20of%20Odisha%2C%20rainforests%20of%20Andamans%2C%20and%20the%20forests%20of%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20the%20Chota%20Nagpur%20Plateau%2C%20and%20Terai%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Raza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20she%20was%20doing%20all%20this%20at%20a%20time%20when%20conservation%2C%20and%20especially%20field%20conservation%2C%20was%20almost%20entirely%20an%20exclusively%20male%20domain.%20In%20her%20younger%20days%2C%20she%20was%20working%20in%20forests%20that%20were%20hardly%20visited%20by%20any%20naturalist%2C%20much%20less%20anyone%20worrying%20about%20their%20conservation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHer%20work%20could%20range%20from%20charting%20up%20a%20management%20plan%20for%20a%20single%20forest%20to%20working%20in%20framing%20a%20nationwide%20policy%20as%20she%20did%20during%20her%20years%20in%20the%20Tiger%20Task%20Force%20or%20as%20an%20important%20member%20involved%20in%20the%20framing%20of%20the%20Wildlife%20(Protection)%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22During%20her%20life%2C%20Anne%20Wright%20received%20a%20myriad%20of%20awards%20for%20her%20conservation%20work.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-333245%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EDuring%20her%20life%2C%20Anne%20Wright%20received%20a%20myriad%20of%20awards%20for%20her%20conservation%20work.%20She%20was%20awarded%20the%20Order%20of%20Golden%20Ark%20by%20Prince%20Bernhard%20of%20Netherlands%20in%201979%2C%20%E2%80%98Most%20Excellent%20Order%20of%20the%20British%20Empire%E2%80%99%20(MBE)%20in%201983%2C%20and%20the%20Sanctuary%20Asia%20Lifetime%20Service%20Award%20in%202013.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMoreover%2C%20what%20strikes%20out%20the%20most%20to%20me%20is%20her%20ability%20to%20forge%20alliances%20over%20common%20cause%20across%20an%20incredibly%20diverse%20set%20of%20people%20and%20stakeholders%20%E2%80%94%20from%20forest%20officers%20to%20politicians%20in%20high%20offices%3B%20from%20businessmen%20to%20communities%20living%20around%20forests%3B%20from%20celebrities%20and%20global%20and%20national%20public%20figures%20to%20young%20school%20kids%3B%20and%20from%20naturalists%20to%20policymakers.%20She%20worked%20with%20everyone%20and%20brought%20them%20together%20for%20the%20cause%20of%20conservation%2C%E2%80%9D%20notes%20Raza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20can%20think%20of%20very%20few%20people%2C%20perhaps%20none%2C%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20conservation%20history%20who%20single-handedly%20worked%20over%20such%20a%20long%20period%2C%20over%20so%20many%20states%2C%20and%20with%20so%20many%20diverse%20sets%20of%20peoples%20and%20interests%20in%20such%20harmony%2C%20and%20brought%20about%20such%20remarkable%20results.%20And%20of%20course%20who%20can%20forget%20the%20power%20of%20her%20pen%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Edited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3B%20Images%20courtesy%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FRazaKazmi17%2Fstatus%2F1710262197698310376%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERaza%20Kazmi%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Wildlife%20Protection%20Society%20of%20India%20(WPSI)%2FFacebook%20and%20Kipling%20Camp%2FFacebook)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698676639000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D333222%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%204%20October%2C%202023%2C%20India%20mourned%20the%20loss%20of%20Anne%20Wright%2C%20a%20pioneering%20conservationist%20who%20dedicated%20over%20five%20decades%20to%20protecting%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20wildlife.%20Wildlife%20historian%20Raza%20Kazmi%20highlights%20Anne%E2%80%99s%20significant%20contributions%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20Wildlife%20Protection%20Act%2C%20Project%20Tiger%2C%20and%20the%20establishment%20of%20the%20Palamau%20Tiger%20Reserve.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Rinchen%20Norbu%20Wangchuk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F333222%2Fanne-wright-conservationist-wildlife-protection-act-reserves-project-tiger-legacy-raza-kazmi%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Facebook%20and%20Instagram%20launch%20ad-free%20subscription%20tier%20in%20EU%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698676610000%2C%22v