nt%20also%20argued%20that%20the%20resolution%20did%20not%20condemn%20the%20terrorism%20of%20Hamas.%20Is%20terrorism%20the%20most%20important%20issue%20at%20this%20moment%3F%20Or%20is%20it%20the%20lives%20of%20the%20thousands%20of%20Gaza%20residents%20who%20are%20being%20constantly%20bombarded%20by%20Israel%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETerrorism%20is%20a%20way%20in%20which%20a%20solitary%20act%20causes%20fear%20or%20terror%20in%20a%20large%20population%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20directly%20or%20immediately%C2%A0impacted%20by%20that%20act%2C%20instilling%20in%20them%20a%20fear%20of%20uncertainty%2C%20and%20that%20it%20can%20happen%20to%20them%20at%20any%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAny%20ideology%20%E2%80%93%20leftist%2C%20religious%20nationalism%20or%20even%20secularism%20%E2%80%93%20can%20use%20terrorist%20methods.%20We%20have%20seen%20this%20many%20times%20not%20only%20in%20the%20history%20of%20the%20last%20century%20but%20also%20this%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20large%20population%20can%20be%20intimidated%20by%20creating%20terror.%20Governments%20use%20this%20technology%20of%20terror%20frequently%20to%20subjugate%20populations.%20But%20then%20it%20is%20considered%20legitimate.%20For%20example%2C%20when%20on%20a%20normal%20day%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20or%20in%20Gaza%2C%20Israeli%20settlers%20entering%20the%20house%20of%20a%20Palestinian%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FInternational%2FwireStory%2Fisraeli-settler-shoots-kills-palestinian-harvester-violence-surges-104457880%5C%22%3Ekilling%20them%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20arresting%20them%20is%20also%20a%20terrorist%20act.%20It%20instils%20fear%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20other%20Palestinians.%20Israelis%20have%20committed%20these%20acts%20repeatedly%20over%20the%20last%2075%20years.%20The%20whole%20world%20knows%20this.%20But%20there%20is%20no%20outcry%20over%20these%20regular%20acts%20of%20terror.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EThe%20horrific%20violence%20of%20October%207%20has%20happened%20and%20cannot%20be%20undone%20by%20any%20intervention%20from%20the%20world%20authorities.%20Its%20aftermath%20must%20be%20dealt%20with.%20Hamas%20needs%20to%20be%20persuaded%20and%20pressurised%20to%20release%20the%20civilian%20hostages%20but%20that%20cannot%20be%20achieved%20by%20obliterating%20the%20people%20of%20Gaza.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20remains%20from%20that%20horrific%20act%20is%20the%20question%20of%20the%20fate%20of%20more%20than%20200%20civilians%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fwhat-do-we-now-about-hamas-hostages-2023-10-19%2F%5C%22%3Ewho%20have%20been%20taken%20hostage%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Hamas.%20The%20world%20needs%20to%20intervene%20for%20their%20freedom.%20That%20requires%20negotiation%20and%20pressure.%20And%20any%20act%20of%20revenge%2C%20like%20ravaging%20the%20whole%20of%20Gaza%20in%20the%20name%20of%20weeding%20out%20Hamas%20fighters%20is%20not%20helping%20the%20cause%20of%20those%20who%20have%20been%20abducted.%20But%20Israel%20seems%20to%20be%20least%20concerned%20with%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20continues%20is%20violence%20%E2%80%93%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20mass%20murder%20and%20genocide%20%E2%80%93%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20the%20most%20important%20thing%20is%20to%20save%20the%20unarmed%20people%20of%20Gaza.%20More%20than%208%2C000%20Palestinians%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fisrael-hamas-war-news-10-29-2023-de1a7d660ba2f6d80b3d7aeaae5bb0f3%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20killed%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Israeli%20bombings%20since%20October%208.%20If%20the%20deaths%20of%20children%20melt%20our%20hearts%2C%20Israel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Fworld%2Fvideo%2Fchildren-of-war-israel-hamas-war-is-destroying-childhood-for-hundreds-in-gaza-2451940-2023-10-21%5C%22%3Eis%20killing%3C%2Fa%3E%20approximately%20100%20children%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20governments%20in%20the%20US%20and%20the%20UK%20are%20not%20only%20shamelessly%20watching%20this%20massacre%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-politics-67151404%5C%22%3Ethey%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhats-behind-rishi-sunaks-hypocrisy-on-israel-palestine%5C%22%3Eare%20also%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F17%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fbiden-israel-gaza-anger.html%5C%22%3Erationalising%20it%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20are%20finding%20justifications%20for%20this%20mass%20murder.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20president%20and%20his%20cabinet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Finternational%2Fworld-news%2Fhamas-hiding-behind-palestinian-civilians-joe-biden%2Fvideoshow%2F104712851.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ehave%20argued%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20%E2%80%98cowardly%E2%80%99%20Hamas%20is%20hiding%20among%20the%20Palestinians.%20What%20can%20poor%20Israel%20do%3F%20It%20is%20forced%20to%20kill%20these%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20also%20be%20said%20that%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20US%20and%20the%20UK%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Farticle%2Fuk-rishi-sunak-criticism-antonio-guterres-united-nations-feud-israel-hamas-conflict%2F%5C%22%3Ehave%20provided%3C%2Fa%3E%20arguments%20to%20justify%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20massacre%20in%20Gaza.%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20attack%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fspeeches-remarks%2F2023%2F10%2F18%2Fremarks-by-president-biden-on-the-october-7th-terrorist-attacks-and-the-resilience-of-the-state-of-israel-and-its-people-tel-aviv-israel%2F%5C%22%3Ewas%20called%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20biggest%20attack%20on%20Jews%20since%20the%20%E2%80%98Holocaust%E2%80%99.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2F2023%2Foct%2F24%2Fisrael-gaza-palestinians-holocaust%5C%22%3Edishonesty%20of%20this%20argument%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20so%20obvious%20that%20there%20is%20no%20need%20to%20say%20anything%20about%20it%20separately.%20By%20saying%20this%2C%20Israel%20is%20seemingly%20granted%20a%20free%20licence%20to%20take%20any%20step.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20people%20in%20Israel%20who%20have%20been%20victims%20of%20Hitler%E2%80%99s%20anti-Semitism%20and%20genocide.%20Many%20of%20them%20have%20repeatedly%20said%20that%20Western%20leaders%20are%20over-emphasising%20their%20commitment%20to%20anti-Semitism%20to%20hide%20the%20guilt%20over%20their%20own%20role%20during%20the%20times%20of%20Hitler.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20historical%20truth%20that%20European%20countries%20and%20the%20US%20closed%20their%20doors%20to%20those%20Jews%20who%20were%20seeking%20to%20escape%20Nazi%20violence.%20After%20the%20World%20War%2C%20these%20countries%20instead%20sent%20them%20to%20the%20land%20of%20the%20Arabs%2C%20saying%20that%20they%20could%20build%20their%20own%20country%20in%20Palestine.%20To%20date%2C%20Europe%20and%20America%20have%20not%20accepted%20their%20discrimination%20against%20the%20Jews.%20They%20themselves%20are%20responsible%20for%20the%20murder%20and%20death%20of%20millions%20of%20Jews%20who%20could%20have%20been%20saved%20had%20they%20been%20granted%20asylum.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20they%20have%20helped%20in%20the%20ethnic%20cleansing%20of%20Palestinians.%20The%20first%20major%20ethnic%20cleansing%20took%20place%20in%201948%2C%20which%20Palestinians%20remember%20as%20the%20%3Cem%3ENakba%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Millions%20of%20Palestinians%20were%20evicted%20from%20their%20land%2C%20homes%2C%20and%20were%20made%20refugees%20in%20their%20own%20homeland.%20Thousands%20were%20killed.%20And%20that%E2%80%99s%20how%20Israel%20was%20created.%20The%20creation%20of%20Israel%20was%20a%20catastrophe%20for%20the%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGenocide%20has%20not%20stopped%20since%201948.%20Israel%20is%20committing%20this%20crime%20every%20day%20at%20the%20instigation%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20powerful%20countries.%20It%20has%