AD%20%7C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fno-bail-for-aaps-manish-sisodia-from-supreme-court-in-liquor-policy-case-4526642%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BMoney%20Trail%20Tentatively%20Established%26quot%3B%3A%20No%20Supreme%20Court%20Relief%20For%20Manish%20Sisodia%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%2041-page%20order%20the%20top%20court%20also%20noted%20the%20CBI's%20claim%20that%20the%20now-withdrawn%20policy%20%26quot%3Bfavoured%20and%20promoted%20cartelisation%26quot%3B%2C%20pointing%20to%20the%20permit%20granted%20to%20Indo%20Spirit%20despite%20several%20such%20complaints.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20court%20also%20noted%20the%20claim%20a%20Rs%202.2%20crore%20bribe%20was%20paid%20to%20Mr%20Sisodia%20by%20Amit%20Arora%2C%20via%20businessman%20Dinesh%20Arora%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20a%20charge%20or%C2%A0allegation%20made%20in%20chargesheet%20filed%20by%20CBI%26quot%3B.%20The%20court%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20may%20be%20difficult%20to%20regard%20alleged%20payment%20as%20a%20'proceed%20of%20crime'%20(under%20PMLA).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Sisodia%20can%20apply%20for%20bail%20again%20after%20three%20months%2C%20a%20two-judge%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20and%20SVN%20Bhatti%20said.%20Earlier%20the%20court%20had%20said%20Manish%20Sisodia%20could%20not%20be%20kept%20in%20jail%20indefinitely.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3EWhat%20Did%20Supreme%20Court%20Say%20In%20Manish%20Sisodia%20Bail%20Plea%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20noted%20the%20CBI's%20claim%20that%20the%20previous%20policy%20had%20been%20modified%20to%20facilitate%20bribes%20from%20wholesale%20distributors%20by%20enhancing%20their%20commission%20from%20five%20per%20cent%20to%2012%20per%20cent.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20change%2C%20the%20court%20said%2C%20meant%20they%20earned%20seven%20per%20cent%20more%20commission%20for%20the%2010%20months%20the%20policy%20was%20in%20place.%20This%20figure%2C%20which%20%26quot%3Bc