ost-of-living-crisis-could-be-eased%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ehere%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20minister%20of%20finance%20and%20corporate%20affairs%20Nirmala%20Sitaraman%20has%20time%20and%20again%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Fpolicy%2Fwriting-off-does-not-mean-completely-waiving-money-due-from-npas-nirmala-sitharaman%2Farticleshow%2F90507965.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estated%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20%E2%80%98write%20off%E2%80%99%20does%20not%20mean%20relief%20to%20the%20borrower.%20The%20rich%20corporate%20borrowers%2C%20who%20are%20usually%20the%20beneficiaries%20of%20such%20write-offs%20by%20banks%2C%20remain%20liable%20for%20repayment%20and%20the%20process%20of%20recovery%20continues%2C%20the%20minister%20has%20asserted.%20Banks%20continue%20to%20pursue%20recovery%20actions%20initiated%20for%20written-off%20accounts%20through%20various%20mechanisms.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20a%20borrower%20fails%20to%20pay%20back%20a%20loan%2C%20it%20is%20termed%20as%20a%20non-performing%20asset%20(NPA)%20under%20conditions%20laid%20down%20by%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India.%20But%20banks%20are%20required%20to%20compensate%20for%20the%20loans%20classified%20as%20NPAs%2C%20an%20exercise%20known%20as%20%E2%80%98provisioning%E2%80%99%20in%20banking%20terms.%20This%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pdicai.org%2FDocs%2FRBI-2023-24-26_95202315256513.PDF%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eprovision%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20made%20by%20setting%20aside%20some%20amount%20from%20the%20bank%E2%80%99s%20profits%20on%20an%20annual%20basis%20as%20stipulated%20by%20the%20RBI.%20Over%20a%20period%20with%20a%20provision%20of%20about%20100%25%2C%20such%20NPAs%20are%20then%20removed%20from%20the%20asset%20books%20of%20banks%20and%20are%20known%20as%20write-offs.%20Bank%20professionals%20or%20chartered%20accountants%20too%20argue%20that%20a%20write-off%20is%20purely%20a%20balance%20sheet%20exercise%2C%20to%20reduce%20a%20bank%E2%80%99s%20tax%20liability.%20They%20argue%20that%20the%20accounts%20that%20are%20earmarked%20for%20write-off%20are%20normally%20100%25%20provided.%20Thus%20while%20writing%20off%20the%20accounts%2C%20banks%20are%20not%20put%20to%20loss%20at%20least%20in%20the%20balance%20sheet.%20%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20merely%20compensating%20for%20NPAs%20and%20bad%20loans%20from%20profits%20made%20elsewhere%20does%20not%20take%20away%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20write-offs%20constitute%20a%20huge%20drain%20on%20public%20money%20entrusted%20with%20banks.%20In%20addition%2C%20they%20constitute%20a%20bonanza%20for%20the%20big%20defaulters.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EA%20bonanza%20for%20corporate%20defaulters%2C%20a%20burden%20on%20the%20public%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fbanks-wrote-off-rs-14-56-lakh-crore-since-2014-15-govt%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ebanks%20have%20written%20off%20Rs%2014.56%20lakh%20crore%20between%202014-15%20and%202022-23.%20The%20share%20of%20large%20industries%20and%20services%20in%20the%20written-off%20amount%20is%20Rs%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E7%2C40%2C968%20crore%20or%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2048.36%25.%20The%20amount%20recovered%20during%20the%20period%20is%20a%20mere%20Rs%202.05%20lakh%20crore%20or.%2014.07%25%20of%20the%20write-offs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20simple%20question%20arising%20out%20of%20these%20figures%20is%2C%20who%20pays%20for%20the%20remaining%20amount%20of%2086%25%20of%20unrecovered%20write-offs%3F%20It%20is%20the%20respective%20banks%20that%20ultimately%20bear%20the%20burden%20and%20this%20is%20precisely%20the%20reason%20why%20banks%20had%20to%20book%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Farticle%2Ffinance%2Fturnaround-of-psbs-from-rs-85k-cr-loss-in-2017-to-nearing-rs-1-trn-profit-123010400818_1.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elosses%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20amounting%20to%20Rs%202%2C07%2C329%20crore%20successively%20for%20five%20years%20from%202015-16%20to%202019-20.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20borrowers%20continue%20to%20be%20liable%20for%20repayment%2C%20in%20practice%20banks%20are%20compelled%20to%20forgo%20any%20hope%20of%20recovery.%20Thus%2C%20in%20practice%2C%20a%20write-off%20becomes%20not%20only%20a%20waiver%20but%20a%20sort%20of%20debt%20relief%20to%20the%20borrowers%20in%20which%20predominantly%20corporates%20have%20a%20major%20share.%20%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20shown%20by%20how%20NPAs%20have%20been%20brought%20down%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20amount%20of%20provision%20on%20account%20of%20non-performing%20assets%20for%20the%20period%202010%20to%202015%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D2947557%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERs%202%2C43%2C935%20crore%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3Cspan%3E%20which%20rose%20to%20a%20whopping%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facrobat.adobe.com%2Fid%2Furn%3Aaaid%3Asc%3AAP%3Ab9d3ebb1-8b9e-4835-acbf-a8b61712be2d%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERs%2021%2C48%2C906%20crore%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20the%20period%202017%20to%202022.%20This%20shows%20that%20the%20write-off%20exercise%20not%20only%20entailed%20a%20relief%20to%20big%20borrowers%20but%20also%20involved%20the%20transfer%20of%20a%20share%20of%20profits%20towards%20provisioning%20for%20bad%20loans.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20continued%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesstoday.in%2Findustry%2Fbanks%2Fstory%2Fno-public-sector-bank-faced-loss-in-april-dec-quarter-of-fy22-govt-326153-2022-03-16%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3El